[2]
Date: Mon, 22 April 2013
Source: The Poultry site [edited]
http://www.thepoultrysite.com/poultrynews/28737/mexico-reports-11-new-h7n3-flu-outbreaks


Mexico Reports 11 New H7N3 Flu Outbreaks
----------------------------------------
There were 11 new outbreaks of highly pathogenic avian influenza (HPAI) of the H7N3 subtype during the last month.

The veterinary authority has sent Follow Up Report No.5 dated 17 Apr to the World Organisation for Animal Health (OIE).

The report outlines 11 new outbreaks of H7N3 HPAI starting between 4 Mar and 4 Apr 2013. A total of 664 126 poultry were involved, among which there were 8505 cases and 502 birds died.

Of the new outbreaks, 6 were in Jalisco, 4 in Guanajuato and one in Tlaxcala. 6 outbreaks were on commercial layer farms (4 in Jalisco and 2 in Guanajuato), 3 on heavy breeder farms (one in Jalisco and 2 in Guanajuato), one in broilers (Jalisco) and one in backyard poultry (Tlaxcala). An epidemiological investigation is on-going in this last outbreak.

Several outbreaks were identified from virus isolated in previously immunised flocks, which did not show clinical signs nor drop in production, according to the OIE report.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[Follow-up report No 5 was submitted to the OIE by Mexico on 17 Apr 2013; it is available, with an interactive map, at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?reportid=13252.

HPAI H7N3 has been circulating in Mexico since June 2012. Mass vaccinations have been applied. - Mod.AS]

